  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.5\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n$ bzzup --default /path/to/index.html --recursive\r\n123abc....\r\n\r\nshould assign path/to/index.html to the empty path resulting in \r\nbzzi://123abc..../\r\nto resolve to that.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nwhen uploading a directory to swarm, bzzup does not currently assign anything to the root, ie. \r\ncreates no manifest entry with empty path that would then map the roothash or domain to a content\r\n(similar to index.html -> \"\" rewrite rules\r\n",
